subject: Re: [Read_Alphabet] Call of Cth ulhu: adjust "This verbal jumble…'Cthul hu' and 'R'lyeh'."
msgSnippet: the dictionary tells me I m wrong, but I say and QS it as s@b tErin. Vin
messageBody:
the dictionary tells me I'm wrong, but I say and QS it as s@b'tErin.
Vin

On 5/23/2013 11:59 PM, Nathan Sharfi wrote:
 

From <https://github.com/adiabatic/qs-literature/commit/5278e3608d778a89c8935567d9a743d0f9ec7f42>:

- add [j] to "minuteness"
- s/v,/visitor,/
- s/ k / cult / (with .Utter for [V])
- "imagery" as [ImIdZrI]

At this point I should probably mention that Lovecraft isn't for the QS novice unless an Orthodox version is handy; [s@bt@rin] seemed like "sub tureen" (unexpected, but I've been thrown bigger curve balls before) until I flipped over to the Orthodox version and read "subterrene".
